# OPTIONAL: YouTube Music authentication headers
#
# The bridge works WITHOUT this file (anonymous mode) — search and playback
# of freely available tracks work out of the box. Adding your own headers
# enables your personal playlists, library and (with Premium) higher quality.
#
# HOW TO CREATE headers.txt:
#   1. Open https://music.youtube.com in your browser and log in.
#   2. Open DevTools (F12) → Network tab.
#   3. Click any request to music.youtube.com (e.g. "browse").
#   4. Copy the REQUEST headers (raw) — the block containing "cookie: ..."
#   5. Paste them into a file named headers.txt in this directory.
#   6. Uncomment the headers.txt volume mount in docker-compose.yml.
#
# Details: https://ytmusicapi.readthedocs.io/en/stable/setup/browser.html
#
# ⚠️  SECURITY WARNING:
#   headers.txt contains your Google session cookies. Treat it like a password:
#   - NEVER commit it to git (it is in .gitignore — keep it there)
#   - NEVER share it or paste it into issues/screenshots
#   - Anyone with this file can access your Google account session
